
E  =  text on examine
US  =  text on use while object is in the scene (not in inventory)
U <on obj>  =  text when object in inventory is used on obj
T  =  text on talk
text  =  general text in dialogue box
text/char  =  text spoken by char
[old state  ->  new state]  =  graphical changes made 
Takable  =  item can be added to the inventory
NT  =  Not Takable

Note: The Grocery Store has a front and back

GROCERY STORE FRONT
Credit Card Terminal
E: This is where I can pay for the bacon

Credit Card Terminal (Unpurchased Bacon in inventory)
E: This is where I can pay for the bacon
Note: Use the credit card on the terminal, see Itemtext for script

Credit Card Terminal (Bacon already purchased)
E: No need to pay twice... 

NOTE: If the player tries to leave the scene before purchasing the bacon:
Text: A true hero can't just steal things...
      I better pay for this bacon!

GROCERY STORE BACK
Bacon
E: Wow... Look at all that bacon!!!!!!!

Bacon (Credit Card NOT in inventory)
Take: Text: But I have no way to pay for the bacon...
            A true hero can't just steal things...
            
Bacon (Credit Card in inventory)
Takable
